author: Giorgio Mendoza
description: Luckfox has introduced the PicoKVM, a compact IP KVM tool for remote control of PCs, servers, and development boards. It uses HDMI and USB for out-of-band management without requiring software on the target device, offering isolated operation independent of the host system. title: Luckfox PicoKVM Lightweight IP KVM Remote Management Tool

author: Giorgio Mendoza
description: Jetway has unveiled the B420UADN1, a fanless compact box PC built around Intel’s Alder Lake-N platform. Designed for industrial and embedded use, the system combines silent operation with high-speed networking, modern display interfaces, and broad OS support. title: Jetway B420UADN1 Compact Box PC with Intel N97, DDR5, and Configurable Security
